author: JoJo Lee
text: Nice and clean gym! The staff are always friendly and welcoming  special thanks to Rayn who helped me sign up for my membership. She‚Äôs super helpful and makes the whole experience enjoyable every time I train here. Love the little bread station where you can recharge before or after a workout, such a thoughtful detail! This branch is also less crowded in the afternoons, which makes it extra comfortable to train. Highly recommend üëç

author: FAZIL PK
text: Offering your hardworking crew not just any old gym membership but an Anytime Fitness experience. Think of it as a wellness partnership that helps your company weave wellness into the fabric of your culture, so everyone can thrive.

author: Haziq Sha'aban
text: I have been a member since its opening. Over time it has gone through many face lifts - new machines, weights and stretching area to keep up with the trend. Its equipment is up to date and sufficient to have a complete workout. While it can be quite crowded during the peak hours, the gym is practically yours the entire time. BONUS points - healthy light snacks are readily available, basic toiletries with clean toilet, and members are allowed to utilise the Body Composition machine. Helps a lot with progress tracking. Lastly, kudos to the staff for being friendly, helpful and keeping the gym in tip top condition.

author: Nikasius Dirgahayu
text: The equipment is complete, with 3 unisex bathrooms and 1 toilet. There are 3 squat racks, 3 treadmills, and the space, although not very large, is well-equipped and comfortable with an organized layout. The location is strategic.

author: Lucien Lim
text: A well equipped and maintained branch of AF. I appreciate the high ceilings as they help with ventilation and allow for space to breathe between sets. The toilets are clean.

author: Tako Boy
text: Accompanied my friend to this gym and was happy to a familiar face as rayn became the gym manager at this outlet ! Which made me felt super wwelcome !

author: bernard duke
text:
I recently joined this gym and have been thoroughly impressed with the experience. The standout feature for me is the incredibly friendly staff, who consistently greet every member with a warm smile. Their welcoming attitude creates a positive and motivating atmosphere, making every visit enjoyable.

Although the gym is small and may seem under-equipped compared to larger facilities, they do an excellent job of maintaining a clean and organized environment. The equipment available is sufficient for all basic gym requirements, ensuring that members can achieve their fitness goals without any major hindrances.

Overall, the combination of friendly staff and a well-maintained facility makes this gym a great choice for anyone looking to stay fit and healthy. I highly recommend it and am happy to rate it 5 stars for its outstanding service and community-oriented approach.

author: Haqqul Azmi
text:
Honest Review:

Gym is small but space efficient. So obviously they can‚Äôt have all types of machine. They have adequate equipment to do a proper workout. Aircon is good, they have WC as well as shower. Water cooler cold and conveniently placed. Parking may be challenging if you come in the day

author: Gannon Waye
text: As staff of this brand I am disgusted at the price they charge for casual pass! This gym is tiny and offers extremely limited options to workout and yet they charge $170 Singapore dollars for 7days to non members / tourists! Never have I been more disappointed in a business and ripping off people. At least be a decent enough establishment. Don‚Äôt waste ur time. ACTIVE SG just around the corner is $3 per visit :) much better

author: Emily Shoup
text: This gym is not for vacationers! A day pass is 33 Singapore dollars (that is more expensive than any gym I‚Äôve ever used in the states or Europe) and non-members can only work out from 12-8. Not ideal times when you have limited time to spend. The space was also tiny which would have been fine if it hadn‚Äôt been so expensive. There are other less expensive gyms in the area.

text:
It is a very compact gym tucked in the corner of Kallang nearer to beach road. If you happened to be around the corner, do check out this gym to burn some calories after meals. There are less than 10 members at any time.

Ample equipment for a small gym like this. This gym is always sanitized by a full time day ops lady so the gym is well maintained in top notch hygiene conditions.

Nice and approachable staff and already ready to assist and help.

Be safe hor!!

author: Kien Kieu
text: Pretty good, if not excellent, AF gym. Standard two racks and a smith machine, but other than than there are a variety of other machines as well. Free weight area is just nice. All cardio machines are separated by screens, so none left unutilised. I think what I personally liked best was that the overall gym was very clean, and all weight slots were clearly labelled, showing the management is very organized.

author: Juliet Li
text:
Great gym to workout.

But I cannot say the same for some of the un-hygienic gym members here. I often find pee stains, pees on the toilet seats. Equipments (dumb bells and bar bells especially) left on the floor and didn't re-rack after their workout

Some gym members who are sick and wish to work out, cough loudly & openly while working out, spreading germs to other gym members who are there to work out. Very "considerate" huh?

The gym coaches are friendly too!

Just remember to bring your access pass for entry. If not, you're not allow to enter & any member open the door for you will liable a $30 fine for them.

If you have a friend who is a gym member here, ask them to bring you here. So that both of you can work out together!

author: Mister CH
text:
It's Anytime fitness.
I've been to other centers before, and this gym was pretty standard. The only reason I'm giving this one 3 stars out of 5 is because i witnessed a few things that kinda disturbed me.

There was a gentleman here doing his leg raises on the bench, and apparently he decided it'd be a good idea to pick a dumbell with his barefeet to add some more intensity to his workout.
I saw that over and over, day after another..  and ewwwww... No offense or disrespect is intended but c'mon bruh.. that's not what dumbells are for.
The staff didn't seem to mind.. so I decided to stick to barbels and machines only..

author: Kevin
text: Thank you for your review! We truly appreciate you taking the time to share your thoughts. We are always striving to provide the best experience possible, and we would love to know how we can improve to earn that fifth star from you.
